Class StatsSvc

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.enremmeta.rtb.jersey.StatsSvc
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JerseySvc

    @Path(value="/stats")
public class StatsSvc
extends Object
implements JerseySvc
    Services to react to things that happen after a successful bid. Called StatsSvc because this is where logging of most of important statistics happens.

                                                       @HeaderParam(value="x-real-ip")
                                                       String xrip,
                                                       @QueryParam(value="lot49version")
                                                       String lot49Version,
                                                       @QueryParam(value="nodeId")
                                                       String nodeId)
        Cookie-related handler. Most important parameter is phase, others are mostly for logging.
        Parameters:
        phase - at the moment, one of the following:
        • rest - RESET - creates a new cookie (see Utils.createModUidCookie()) and sends it as a response with a redirect to self with a sync phase
        • sync - SYNCHRONIZE - sends a redirect to the partner-initiated sync URI for the given exchange, if available. Otherwise, just returns a pixel.
        See Also:
        ExchangeAdapter.getPartnerInitiatedSyncUrl(String), Utils.createModUidCookie(), Utils.cookieToLogModUid(String), Utils.logToCookieModUid(String)
